      • checkMandatoryFields

        boolean checkMandatoryFields()

        Returns:
        True, if mandatory fields is correct

      • packAsString

        java.util.Map<ResponseFieldsList,​java.lang.String> packAsString()
        Packed all received fields into string. Exclude all arrays. All enum in first transform into their storage type, such as String, int, etc. After writes into String To get arrays info, you must call this method on every array element.
        Returns:
        The map, contains pairs of ResponseFieldsList and String-view of field

      • packAsObject

        java.util.Map<ResponseFieldsList,​java.lang.Object> packAsObject()
        Packed all received fields into object. All fields writes into map as-is, cast to Object. For example, arrays will be write as Set IResponse . Primitive types writes as wrappers. For access to field data you mast cast their type
        Returns:
        the map, contains pairs of ResponseFieldsList and casted to Object fields.
